You are debugging a production issue where a Spring-based dynamic rules execution service suffers from a gradual increase in Metaspace usage, eventually throwing `java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Metaspace` after a few days of continuous operation. The heap allocation remains low and stable during this process. The core execution logic is as follows:

java
@Service
public class RuleExecutor {
    public void execute(String ruleCode) {
        try {
            ByteArrayClassLoader classLoader = new ByteArrayClassLoader(this.getClass().getClassLoader());
            Class<?> ruleClass = classLoader.defineClass("Rule_" + System.nanoTime(), compileToBytecode(ruleCode));
            Runnable ruleInstance = (Runnable) ruleClass.getDeclaredConstructor().newInstance();
            ruleInstance.run();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            throw new RuntimeException(e);
        }
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue in a high-concurrency Spring Boot application. A thread-safe configuration manager bean holds a reference to a configuration object that is updated periodically. Under heavy concurrent read/write traffic, consumer threads occasionally experience a `NullPointerException` or read default values (e.g., `0` or `null`) from the configuration properties, even though the configuration writer thread always passes fully populated data to the constructor. The implementation is as follows:

java
public class ConfigurationHolder {
    private RuntimeConfig config;

    public void refreshConfiguration(Map<String, String> properties) {
        this.config = new RuntimeConfig(properties);
    }

    public RuntimeConfig getConfig() {
        return this.config;
    }
}
